news.title: Reliance Industries enters commercial real estate business
news.para: "The company has incorporated a wholly owned subsidiary named Reliance SOU (RSOUL) to carry on, inter alia, the business of development of properties for commercial use," it said in a BSE filing.

news.title: LG approves draft Delhi master plan-2041
news.para: The Authority in its meeting, also took a decision for relaxation in guidelines pertaining to woman beneficiaries for in situ rehabilitation under the 'Jahan Jhuggi Wahan Makan' programme, the DDA said in a statement.

news.title: Housing finance companies to face headwinds amid rising interest rates: Report
news.para: For the top 12 HFCs, NPAs peaked at 2.9 per cent in FY21, and then marginally improved to 2.8 per cent in FY22. The overall stressed book (defaults and restructured loans) remained around 4 per cent in both FY22 and FY21.

news.title: Navi Mumbai builder Nalin Shah gets clean chit in cheating case
news.para: The Economic Offences Wing (EOW) of Navi Mumbai Crime branch had in July 2018 arrested Shah after the complainant Heena Shaikh (33), a Seawoods resident, had lodged a cheating complaint against him.

news.title: NGT asks if inquiry into green violation held in Mumbai SRA project
news.para: Last year, the NGT had passed an order restraining the builder, Skylark Buildcon and Oberoi Realty, from selling flats in the project’s free sale component till it provided 500 car parks for the slum rehabilitation buildings.

news.title: Nandan Nilekani's NRJN Family Trust sells Bengaluru residential asset for Rs 55 crore
news.para: The property, spread over 9,488 sq ft, is located at 3rd Cross, 3rd Block, Koramangala and was sold to V Seetha, the wife of C Valliappa, an industrialist and the founder of the Sona Valliappa Group (an extension of The Sona Group).

news.title: YEIDA cancels allotment of two plots to Supertech over Rs 86 crore dues
news.para: The developer, however, termed the move illegal citing the insolvency proceedings that were initiated against it in March 2022 for defaulting on payment of Rs 431 crore to a consortium of banks.

news.title: Probe UP-RERA's decision to tweak 2018 order to builder, says Allahabad HC
news.para: “UP-Rera is required to reflect on its working, the manner in which the orders are being passed…,’ said the February 9 order by the two-judge bench of justices Sunita Agarwal and Nand Prabha Shukla.

news.title: Setback for builders in Noida, Greater Noida; SC refuses to recall its Nov 7 order
news.para: The top court had passed various orders including the one issued on June 10, 2020, during the COVID-19 pandemic period, by which it had capped the rate of interest at eight per cent on the dues for land given on lease to several builders in order to provide them the succour.

news.title: Registration of properties in Mumbai falls 11% to 9,268 units in February 2023
news.para: Real estate consultant Knight Frank India in a statement said Mumbai city (area under BMC jurisdiction) saw property sales registration of 9,268 units in February 2023.

news.title: HDFC, Punjab National Bank hike lending rates
news.para: The second-biggest public sector lender, Punjab National Bank (PNB), increased its Marginal Cost of Funds Based Lending Rate (MCLR) by 10 basis points across all tenure.

news.title: Mumbai not for developers; SRA intended for public welfare: Bombay HC
news.para: Afcons Developers Ltd and Ameya Housing Private Ltd were appointed as co-developers of the slum rehabilitation project at Jogeshwari in suburban Mumbai.

news.title: Delhi HC asks centre to take call on whether to accord sanction for attachment of DMRC assets
news.para: The high court granted time to the competent authorities in the central government to take the decision in this regard and place it on record while listing the matter for further hearing on March 2.

news.title: Complete Muttathara flat complex work in 15 months: Kerala CM
news.para: ​The chief minister in the meeting urged the authorities to complete the flat complex work within 15 months. He said there should be constant monitoring for the time-bound completion of this project.

news.title: Haryana government orders probe into Panchkula's MDC plots scam
news.para: ​The scheme for the allotment was notified and issued in the year 2004. Questions were being raised on the allotment of 39 such plots. Also, 120 un-allotted plots are under scanner.
